{
  "texts": [
    "The 27 GeV and 54.4 GeV data were collected in 2017 and 2018 between the first and second phases of the RHIC BES program.",
    "The number of events passing the event-level criterion were 240 and 570 million, respectively.",
    "With an order of magnitude difference of the number of events, combined with the significant energy dependence of heavy flavor hadron production cross section, the precision of the measurements at different energies varies considerably.",
    "The results from the 54.4 GeV collisions have the best precision.",
    "While the full reconstruction of heavy flavor hadrons in these data is not possible because of a lack of silicon vertex devices, the electrons from heavy flavor hadron decays are used as proxy for the heavy flavor hadrons."
  ]
}